This oddity was also released as Bela Lugosi Meets A Brooklyn Gorilla, but no matter what you call it, this is a horror film that will stiffen you with laughter! Also, look for the great Ray ‘Crash’ Corrigan in the gorilla suit…

programme.title: Bowery at Midnight

When things get out of hand, Lugosi kills his henchmen, who wind up as zombies in the cellar. Director Wallace Fox, who had already worked with Lugosi on two previous Monogram films, Spooks Run Wild and The Corpse Vanishes, comes through with a true horror gem.

programme.title: White Zombie (1932)
programme.desc: Watch Bela Lugosi use his special zombie grip to make beautiful women submit to his every desire! In this low budget screamer, a couple honeymooning in Haiti run afoul of a diabolical voodoo master. They’re soon wishing they’d gone to Cancun! This Pre-­Code horror classic is considered to be the first feature length zombie movie, and features great atmospheric direction by Victor Halperin. The film’s unsung hero was set designer Ralph Berger, who exploited sets of previous Universal Studios films, including bits from Dracula, The Hunchback of Notre Dame, and Frankenstein. Whatever you do, DON’T LOOK INTO LUGOSI’S EYES!

programme.title: The Corpse Vanishes

Noted as one of the most successful and imitated collaborations between Monogram and Lugosi, this film’s plot bears an uncanny resemblance to the real world story of the murderous Elizabeth Bathory.

George Zucco, Molly Lamont, and Joyce Compton also star, as well as Angelo Rossitto, (Freaks) as a menacing dwarf with a habit of stepping on Lugosi’s foot!

programme.title: Girl in the Dark (1959)
programme.desc: Mike investigates a case where adopted children are the victims of a blackmailing operation.

programme.title: Dark Star
programme.desc: Little Joe tries to help a gypsy girl who was abandoned by her people - because they believed she was a werewolf.

programme.title: The Clampetts Get Psychoanalyzed
programme.desc: Jethro needs a passing health certificate so he can graduate from fifth grade, so he goes to the only doctor the Clampetts know: Mrs. Drysdale's psychiatrist.

programme.title: The Case of the Diamond Tooth (1955)
programme.desc: While walking along the banks of the River Thames, Watson discovers a diamond tooth. Not long after, Holmes learns that the body of a murder victim had been found near where Watson found the tooth.

programme.title: Just Like Your Father
programme.desc: Medic follows Dr. Konrad Styner and his team of Surgeons as they tackle medical cases inside Los Angeles.

programme.title: The Big Man
programme.desc: New York City police officer Barney Ruditsky faces off against organized crime during the Roaring 20s.

programme.title: The New Years Party
programme.desc: Stanley and Celia end up being separated on New Year's Eve and they spend the night trying to reunite before the strike of midnight.

programme.title: Live My Own Life
programme.desc: Bud moves out of the house and finds that his new found independence is not all that it's cracked up to be.

programme.title: Jack and the Beanstalk
programme.desc: Be happy and go wacky! The classic fairy tale gets a comical workover from comedy legends Abbott and Costello! Lou plays Jack, while former heavyweight boxer Buddy Baer plays the giant who lives in the sky. Meanwhile, renowned voice artist Mel Blanc (Bugs Bunny!) lends his familiar sound to various animals in the story. There’s even a talking harp! This is one film that will make you think twice the next time someone offers you some magic beans...

programme.title: Kept Husbands (1931)
programme.desc: Joel McCrae stars as Jack Brunton, a factory employee who becomes a hero after saving a couple of co-workers from what could've been a fatal accident. As the accolades build, he finds himself marrying the boss' daughter. He's the envy of everyone at the job, but he soon regrets how his life has changed. This RKO Radio Picture also stars Dorothy Mackaill (Love Affair, The Office Wife), and Ned Sparks (Lady for a Day, Gold Diggers of 1933), with direction by Lloyd Bacon (Footlight Parade, Marked Woman).

programme.title: Spy Squad
programme.desc: The year is 1961, and tensions between America and the Communists are at an all-time high. America is preparing to launch a rocket with sensitive information from Cape Canaveral, and the Communists will stop at nothing to get their hands on it. Little do they know, American government agents are wise to their plans, and so the double-crossing begins!

programme.title: Sitting Bull
programme.desc: Major Robert Parrish becomes embroilled in the Battle of Little Big Horn. When he helps Chief Sitting Bull escape, he is charged with crimes against his government. Now facing possible execution, only President Ulysses S. Grant can help him.

programme.title: The Borrowers
programme.desc: A Primetime Emmy went to this production of Mary Norton's famous children's tale. It's all about a little boy (Dennis Larson) who discovers a family of tiny people living under the floorboards of his home. The cast includes Eddie Albert, Tammy Grimes, and Judith Anderson, plus the curmudgeonly Barnard Hughes.

programme.title: Hercules and the Captive Women
programme.desc: Originally released in 1961 as "Ercole alla conquista di Atlantide" in Italy, "Hercules and the Captive Women" is the updated US version released for audiences in 1963. Follow the chronicles of Hercules with Reg Park in his Hercules film debut! Action packed from the beginning, Hercules encounters Ismene (Laura Altan) when he must save her from a shape-shifting creature -- and that's just the beginning! Ismene then brings Hercules to Atlantis where they come face to face with the evil Queen Antinea (Fay Spain), Ismene's mother, and try to prevent her dreams of world conquest. Will Hercules prevail? Find out in "Hercules and the Captive Women."

programme.title: Condemned to Live
programme.desc: When a peaceful European village is suddenly plagued by a string of gruesome murders, the nocturnal attacks are pegged on a mysterious giant bat. But the real culprit is mild-mannered, respectable Paul Kristan, a kindly professor with an enigmatic ailment that transforms him nightly into a bloodthirsty vampire. Directed by horror aficionado Frank R. Strayer and produced independently, this film bears many of the hallmarks of a Universal prestige picture, and was a rarity for its time, considering its relatively sympathetic treatment of vampires.

programme.title: Episode 7
programme.desc: Groucho, Chico and Harpo graced the small screen in the 1950s appearing in a myriad of variety programs, sitcoms, and game shows. The Marx Brothers TV Collection features long-lost material from this wide array of appearances.

programme.title: Carol Burnett Show - Season 1 Episode 11
programme.desc: Guest starring Don Adams and Lesley Anne Warren in a series of comedic sketches hosted by Carol Burnett.

programme.title: Season 11 Episode 99
programme.desc: Comedian Johnny Carson hosts a variety of celebrities in his iconic late night talk show.

programme.title: Mysterious Mr. Wong
programme.desc: Out of the night creeps a shadow, striking terror into the heart of Chinatown! Bela Lugosi plays a power mad psychopath in this thriller from Monogram Pictures. William Nigh directs a tale of kidnapping and intrigue, with a cast that includes Wallace Ford (Freaks, Shadow of a Doubt) as a wiseguy reporter who falls into the diabolical clutches of the sinister Wong, a madman who believes he will one day rule China!

programme.title: Chamber of Horrors
programme.desc: A wealthy lord dies and is entombed with a valuable deposit of jewels. Seven keys are required to unlock the tomb and get hold of the treasure. A series of mysterious events cause the keys to be scattered, and when trying to unravel the circumstances, the heiress of the fortune and her companion investigators become entangled in a web of fraud, deceit, torture, and murder.

programme.title: Dark Night of the Scarecrow
programme.desc: When gentle but mentally challenged Bubba Ritter's young friend Marylee is mauled by a vicious dog, Bubba becomes the town scapegoat. Disguised as a scarecrow to hide from the angry townspeople, Bubba is found out and tragically murdered. But little do his attackers know that justice for Bubba will come from beyond the grave!

programme.title: Anatomy of a Psycho (1961)
programme.desc: Terrifying! A Psychotic Killer prowls the night! ... Will he be stopped before he kills again? Ronnie Burns (the son of TV favorites George Burns and Gracie Allen!) stars as Chet, a delusional young man boiling with rage after his brother is sentenced to death for murder. As his paranoid feelings increase, Chet decides to create some mayhem of his own, including arson! A cast of unknowns come together for this feature by Boris Petroff, who also directed the cult favorite, The Unearthly. Just sit back and enjoy watching poor Chet lose touch with reality!

programme.title: Nose (1958)
programme.desc: Here he is: the one, the only… GROUCHO! Legendary comedian, Groucho Marx, hosts this laugh-a-minute quiz show, where three couples face off, answering questions of varying difficulty. Being transgender, she thought it might be true. After watching "Priscilla Queen of the Desert", Kathryn Gonzales learned what "transgender" meant. After attempting unsuccessfully to transition five times, Kathryn had an epiphany at a stop light and finally found her own path. After making derogatory comments about a gay classmate, Joseph's friend tells him something that changes him forever. When Adam Sandel first moved to San Francisco, he had the pleasure of interviewing out and proud actor Sir Ian McKellen, who gave Adam some advice that changed his life.Jason Daniel Fair has a white, Jewish mother and a black, Christian dad. His dad gave him advice as a child that helped him embrace his differences and shaped who he is as a gay man. Crystal Cheatham was told by her church that she had the voice, an incredible gift of playing the guitar, the ability to lead a band, to write music, and to mentor children. But all that meant nothing to them because she's a "practicing homosexual."

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E1 | Savannah is a ray of light in the LGBTQ+ youth community and she wants to be a Disney animator one day. She is a member of the Mormon church and has been all of her life however when Savannah came out to her to ward during a sacrament meeting a year ago, the Bishop had her microphone turned off, stopping her right before she had wrapped up her speech. She has since become an advocate for LGBTQ+ teens.

programme.title: Room To Grow
programme.desc: S1 E2 | Cody (Elton Cray) is a professional musician & rapper. We did an initial interview with him in his home, then visited with him almost 10 months later at one of his shows. An interesting and passionate man who speaks his mind, Cody's music is about his struggles with himself and others around him who have been indifferent to how he identifies.

programme.title: Good Monsters
programme.desc: Eric Stine, a biracial artist, embarks on a cross country journey of discovery, art, and inspiration. Good Monsters is a colorful film that shows Stine’s struggle to understand how his life and work have been affected by his estranged father.

programme.title: Amplify Voices
programme.desc: S1 E1 | The four most powerful African American women in politics share the story of their friendship and how it has changed politics in America. Join the authors in a discussion about the book and how their careers evolved, while offering advice to Black women who dream of working in the field.

programme.title: Hank
programme.desc: After reluctantly agreeing to an open relationship, middle aged gay man Hank starts a wild journey with a mysterious young man only to find he’s put himself in danger. Narrowly escaping with just his life, and forced to walk home alone and naked in the middle of the night, Hank realizes the compromise he made to save his marriage has gone too far.

programme.title: Coming of Age in Cherry Grove
programme.desc: Founded in 1869, Cherry Grove (Fire Island, NY) is considered by most to be the first openly LGBTQ community in the United States. It has become known as one of the most accepting resort communities in the world – a place where you can not only discover who you are, but also freely experiment with who or what (gender) you may want to become. Cherry Grove is also known for the famous “INVASION” – an annual ritual that takes place every July 4th as a celebration of gender acceptance. This film tells the stories of a variety of long-term residents and what they find so wonderful about life in Cherry Grove.

programme.title: Still I Strive
programme.desc: The NACA orphanage in Phnom Penh, work to achieve one of the highest honors in Cambodian society, to perform before the Princess Bopha Devi. The children's epic performance is recreated as a cinematic adventure that parallels their harrowing backstories.

programme.title: The Library
programme.desc: As we seek to honor and celebrate the countless LGBTQ individuals, communities, sub-communities, and dynasties that have flourished in the face of adversity over decades, it dawned on us that there are so many unknown and untold stories about gay history, vocabulary, vernacular, and the human experiences that fuel the formation of cultures and identities based on authentic self-expression and love. As we discovered these stories, we wished for a gay “library” where anyone could visit and learn, in bite-size portions, about crucial events in gay history, gay heroes and icons past and present, fascinating sub-cultures, slang terms, scientific references, political movements... Essentially, a record of all the bits of queer education that are at risk of being lost or misinterpreted — information that we all crave as members of LGBTQ communities and as Allies. Do you know the story of the first Pride parade? Ever wondered what “Skoliosexual,” “Polycule,” or “Doppelbanger” means? The Library is open — and ready to clue you in.

programme.title: Gay Mean Girls
programme.desc: S1 E1-2 | Lucy is a “very good ally” who stares at her best friend Miranda…. a lot. They hatch a plan to start Gay Prom Royalty together to promote equality at their school. Miranda pays Lucy a visit on a day off from school. We get a glimpse into Lucy’s home life.

programme.title: The QueerX Awards
programme.desc: The circus is in town and just in time for National Coming Out Day! Welcome to the 2021 QueerX Awards brought to you by Lexus. Join us as hosts, Drew Droege and Raneir Pollard, take us on a carnival tour of LGBTQ music, films, and icons! Featuring appearances by Bowen Yang, Michaela Jaé Rodriguez, Patton Oswalt, Dwyane Wade, Erica Wheeler, and Elvira, Mistress of the Dark, Cassandra Peterson. And don’t miss the special performances by Chanel and the Circus, Mila Jam, and Alsace Carcione.

programme.title: Happy Playland
programme.desc: S1 E1-5 | Billie Haare, an anxious actress caught between her passion for stage and her parents’ dreams of the silver screens, starts a new job at a desolate indoor playground, managed by wannabe-insta-star Cris. Billie quickly develops feelings for social justice warrior, Zara, who is sadly 23 and not looking for anything serious. After a passionate moment in the ball pit, Billie and Zara both begin to question what they want. But the playland is soon to be closed - and Billie’s anxiety can only handle so much. Cris decides to intervene. Can Billie woo Zara into forever and always? Will anyone ned up happy? Will Cris’ trip to Queenstown increase her followers? Only time will tell, in the place where dreams come true, Happy Playland, The Wellington branch.

programme.title: A Queer City
programme.desc: Three young drag artists navigate the rising drag scene in Norwich.

programme.title: The Millennial Experience
programme.desc: The Millennial Experience is one part dance-for-film and one part documentary. The film explores cultural appropriation vs appreciation, LGBTQIA+ culture, feminism and how these topics impact the Millennial generation. The dance sequences in the film are adapted from director Alex Crozier's stage production MILLENNIALS which focuses on the aforementioned themes. Fourteen on-camera interviews that expound on the main topics were conducted with people of various ages, ethnicities, sexual orientations, and genders . The Millennial Experience seeks to uplift the voices of women, LGBTQIA+, and BIPOC communities in an effort to create a more equitable and just world.

programme.title: Culture Q
programme.desc: Culture Q is the world’s first weekly queer-centric news series brought to you by the leading global queer streaming network, Revry. This innovative, weekly news series creatively features entertainment, pop culture, lifestyle and political news with wit and insightfully nuanced perspectives. Emphasizing the queer millieu, Culture Q stands to be the leading, weekly forum for boundary-pushing discussions and commentary. Hosted by digital news influencer pioneers, Shira Lazar and Andy Lalwani of the highly successful What’s Trending, Culture Q will feature an ever-changing cavalcade of guests who help capture that X-factor which defines queer culture.

programme.title: The Billionaire
programme.desc: A gender-swapped independent film adaptation of George Bernard Shaw's classic play 'The Millionairess', transposed into a contemporary context of Gay Marriage and Asexuality, THE BILLIONAIRE follows a haughty and prudish young billionaire's quest for love, despite all the odds. The film is a throwback to Classic Hollywood films, stylistically and tonally.

programme.title: Out On Stage
programme.desc: Out On Stage is THE absolutely hilarious and one-of-a-kind, originally produced comedy hosted by Zach Noe Towers! See OUT Magazine's "1 of the 10 comedians to watch in 2018," the comedian that Sarah Silverman calls, "So, SO, SO Funny" and 17 other top-rated Gay and Lesbian stand-up comedians discuss taboo subjects as only they can!

programme.title: Queens & Cowboys
programme.desc: Roping and riding across North America, the International Gay Rodeo Association's courageous cowboys and cowgirls brave challenges both in and out of the arena on their quest to qualify for the World Finals. Along the way, they’ll bust every stereotype in the book. The film tells the story of five members of the IGRA. From Wade Earp, a descendant of cowboy legend Wyatt Earp and one of the best competitors on the circuit, to Char Duran, a female bull rider who’s never won a buckle but seems determined to die trying, “QUEENS & COWBOYS” weaves the stories of its protagonists over the course of an entire rabble-rousing year. An unprecedented look at the strength it takes to be gay in the rural west, this film explores the many struggles threatening the IGRA and the gay community at large, how far society has come on the subject of gay equality, and how far we still have to go.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E3 | Mom and Dad are in town for a visit. Join us as we share a day together in the kitchen - with tomatoes.

programme.title: Jonathan's Kitchen
programme.desc: S1 E4 | Colin McLetchie joins me for a rare and important afternoon of self care.

programme.title: The Dead Mothers Club
programme.desc: The (Dead Mothers) Club tells the story of three women- a Southern artist redefining herself through her art; a high school senior struggling to gain independence; and a Brazilian living in NY, navigating first-time motherhood – all of whom lost their mothers during adolescence. The film reveals how coming of age without their mothers has and continues to play a role in their lives. Structured around a series of ‘dialogues’ featuring Rosie O’Donnell, Molly Shannon and Jane Fonda that focus on various themes threading their stories together, these ruminations allow for heart-breaking and at times humorous insight into how ultimately one’s past can dictate their future. From the cyclical nature of grief to their own mortality, the women of The Club provoke thoughts surrounding the innate, complicated nature of the mother/daughter relationship, even in its absence.

programme.title: Putting On
programme.desc: S2 E4 | On and Dave take a break between life in New York and their new beginning in Los Angeles as they travel to Israel for some reflection. Later on they head to Paris, the city of love, for an intimate wedding ceremony.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E1 | LGBTQ pride and power take center stage on this episode. We’re talking about finding our strength, and Dante Maurice Marshall and Y. Chere Marshall join us as well to talk intersectionality when it comes to being queer and serving our country. Plus, comedian Nicky Paris from The Zoo joins us for some comic relief.

programme.title: The Q Agenda
programme.desc: S2 E2 | We’re joined by Roman Navarrette of The Blade LA, drag queen Kay Sedia, fellow LATV host Dennis Pastorizo, and our host Victor gives us makeup tips!

programme.title: CAPTAIN ORELLANA
programme.desc: Captain Orellana, a private investigator and former cop specializing in the most impossible mysteries, is tapped for the wackiest, most dangerous case of his long career. With a comical 007-like swagger, Orellna gets to the bottom of the uncanny occurrences in a remote village that seems to be ? POSSESSED!

programme.title: OMNIVORES
programme.desc: A prestigious journalist accepts an undercover writing assignment addressing the recent emergence of "clandestine restaurants," one of which holds secret gatherings where diners feast on human flesh in exchange for large sums of money. What started as a simple job may just end in a bloody nightmare.

programme.title: RABBIT WOMAN
programme.desc: A China-born state employee discovers corruption within the Argentinian police force and bravely sets out to bring an end to its corrupt ties to the Chinese mafia. While on the run from the criminals, she discovers a bizarre animal experiment involving rabbits that perversely may hold the key to her success.

programme.title: DIA NARANJA
programme.desc: Three Latin American women from different backgrounds see their fantasies about the future give way to anxiety as they are hit with the same shocking news: they are pregnant. A colorful, vivacious look at the excitement and drama that often accompanies the prospect of motherhood.

programme.title: CAMINO DEL VINO
programme.desc: Tragedy befalls a world-famous sommelier attending an important wine event when he suddenly, inexplicably loses his palate. His mission to recover his talent leads him on a journey through peerless wineries and beautiful vineyards, but most importantly into his own soul.

programme.desc: "Something I really like to talk about is cannabis connoisseurship.” Noted breeder, cultivator, Founder of the Golden Tarp competition, Wonderland Nursery and Port Royal genetics (and Ganjier instructor) Kevin Jodrey as he joins Ganjier Managing Director Derek Gilman to discuss classic cultivars of the 70's & 80's, regenerating lost varietals (namely Skunk), Northeastern terroir, favorite consumption methods and techniques, plus personal preferences for his six-plant cannabis garden.

programme.title: The Dank Duchess
programme.desc: Between the two flowers and the hash, which direction is this gonna take me?" An apt question as we drop into the Lounge for this highly immersive session of High Rollers, featuring internationally recognized cannabis cultivator, hash-maker and writer, the one and only Dank Duchess. Her Niche is Hashish. Based in Oakland, California, The Dank Duchess is a prodigy of legendary master hashishin (and Ganjier instructor) Frenchy Cannoli. In this episode, she and host, Ganjier Managing Director Derek Gilman, discuss the finer points of premium hash-making beginning with source material, hashing out the differences and nuances between cured flower and fresh-frozen cannabis. Next, they the explore a cornucopia of connoisseur consumption creations including bedazzled joints, "This is design, darling, form and function," aka "O-O's" (Orifice Openers) along with a demonstration of proper smoking technique, how to discern quality hash, and conclude with a session involving the ancient chillum - the oldest known cannabis consumption device.

programme.desc: Certification for sustainable, naturally-grown agriculture, Clean Green Certified is the closest to “Organic” that the cannabiz can get. Chris offers tips and tricks that you can put to use in your own garden. Dig in! Founded in 2004, Swami Select has had the pleasure of being Clean Green Certified since 2011.

programme.title: Meet the International Canna Farmer's Association Chair, Kristin Nevedal
programme.desc: We're honored to welcome to today's show, Kristin Nevedal, International Cannabis Farmer's Association Chair. The International Cannabis Farmer’s Association strives to empower traditional Cannabis farmers through education, research and advocacy. Their programs raise public awareness about the benefits of traditionally farmed Cannabis and provide educational resources for farmers, regulators, industry and consumers. They advocate for the development of responsible regulations in CA, which are seen as crucially important due to the state’s significance to national and international policy development. They will promote public policy that ensures an equal share of licenses are issued to traditional sun grown Cannabis farmers. They conduct research to quantify the ecological superiority of traditionally farmed Cannabis as well as gathering data necessary to establish internationally recognized appellations of origin. They create a dynamic and creative consumer direct educational campaign that highlights the quality and ecological superiority of traditionally farmed sun grown Cannabis.

programme.title: What's It Like to Judge The Emerald Cup - Go Backstage with Swami Select
programme.desc: Founded in 2003, Northern California’s Emerald Cup advances the concept of sustainable, outdoor farming of medical cannabis. Longtime advocates of the spiritually and physically healing potential of regeneratively-grown cannabis, Swami Select founders Nikki Lastreto and Swami Chaitanya have judged The Emerald Cup’s flower competition since the event began. As the largest, organic, outdoor, medicinal cannabis competition in the world, The Cup advances our movement by cross-pollinating cultivators, patients and patrons with scientific and agriculture experts who work across industries. Now a global movement, the community celebration honors the year’s best, sun-grown, medicinal cannabis producers.

programme.title: Stepdads The Sketch- Ep 1
programme.desc: When infidelity claims the life of Joanne Bates, her children Lisa and Stevie are left in the custody of her fiancé Mike and his brother Jerry. Mike, a straight-laced, hardworking accountant; and Jerry, a wild, unstable, womanizer were both former foster children and together they provide a unique balance of parenting skills for young Lisa and Stevie. - Step Dads starring Ben Sloane (R.I.P.D, Alpha House), Morocco Omari (Empire, 21 Bridges, Homeland, Chicago Fire), Jorie Binion (Chicago P.D) Charles Dunlap (Chicago Fire, Empire), and Jay Davis (Not Another Black Movie, Choke On That: The Series, Not Another Zombie Movie) is a comedy about two polar opposite foster brothers raising two children using non-traditional parenting methods while shedding a satirical light on the importance of adoption. We poke fun at some of the mishaps which comes along with the shock of being a new parent, but ultimately, we hope to spread awareness on adoption, the importance of having fathers and father-figures in the lives of young people, and having a familial loving environment. The moral of our story is that “No family is perfect, but every child deserves to be loved unconditionally, and raised in a reliable, stable support system.”

programme.title: Not Another Black Movie
programme.desc: Not Another Black Movie stars Damon Williams (Bad Boys of Comedy, Comic View, BET LIVE, The Tom Joyner Morning Show), Janet Hubert (The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air), Rodney Perry (The Monique Show, Who's Got Jokes) Jay Davis (Not Another Zombie Movie, Shots Fired), and Leon Rogers (WGCI, Comic View, Bad Boys of Comedy). - Not Another Black Movie is not only a spoof of a genre often associated with Tyler Perry films, but a satirical look at family dysfunction as well. Written by Jay Davis and Directed by Donte "Diesel" Williams, Not Another Black Movie addresses issues that effect many families whether they be rich or poor, black or white. Although we poke fun at some of the stereotypical roles portrayed in this genre, we hope to shed some light on problems that plague many families while giving you a good laugh.

programme.title: Europa
programme.desc: Discovering and exploring Jupiter's most promising moon, Europa. Europa was named after a Phoenician noblewoman who was abducted by Zeus after he had transformed himself into a bull. Rather fittingly, Zeus established Europa on the island of Crete as its queen, where he had several children with her, including Minos, the legendary king of Crete. In later ages, the continent of Europe would be named after Europa.

programme.title: Jupiter
programme.desc: Jupiter is the fifth planet from our Sun and is, by far, the largest planet in the solar system – more than twice as massive as all the other planets combined. Jupiter’s stripes and swirls are actually cold, windy clouds of ammonia and water, floating in an atmosphere of hydrogen and helium. Jupiter’s iconic Great Red Spot is a giant storm bigger than Earth that has raged for hundreds of years.

programme.title: Germany's Via Julia
programme.desc: Discover the ancient Roman military road Via Julia that made rapid travel from Lutetia (now Paris) to Constantinople (now Istanbul) possible. Meet the people who keep the memories of this ancient route intact, and who do their utmost to keep the sacred traditions of their ancestors alive.

programme.title: The Road of Livingstone
programme.desc: “The Road of Livingstone” is a long journey in the footsteps of the British explorer David Livingstone along the Zambezi River, from its mouth in Mozambique all the way to Victoria Falls, at the border of Zambia and Zimbabwe.

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Elements of a Great Bar
programme.desc: Join Tony on his quest to characterize the perfect bar in New York City. Discover the importance of a maniacal bartender, the proper chemical makeup of drinks, the joys of seedy dive-bars, and the need for late-night snacks.

programme.title: Belize
programme.desc: Un-Belizable! We are off on a Central American Mayan excursion. We head up the steps of the ancient high temple at Lamanai. Then we take a city tour of the main tourist destination, Belize City. We learn about Belize's colonial roots at the Belize City History Museum and dive the amazing Blue Hole.

programme.title: Ottawa
programme.desc: We visit Canada's capital city-on-a-hill in Ottawa, Ontario. Sail down the famous Rideau Canal locks, go deep into Ottawa's Cold War history at the Diefenbunker, and explore Canada's military history at the Canadian War Museum. Then, head up the Peace Tower and visit the Library of Parliament.

programme.title: Mexico - A Desert Between Two Seas
programme.desc: The Baja Peninsula juts out into the Pacific Ocean like an icicle. The dazzling arid peninsula is a succession of sunset-kissed beaches and trickling creeks. Each year, millions of whales come to reproduce in the preserved waters of the peninsula that their whale ancestors knew so well.

programme.title: South Africa - A Rainbow Nation
programme.desc: With its wide-open spaces and pristine coastline, the province of KwaZulu-Natal has become one of South Africa's ecotourism havens. Away from the carefree atmosphere of its beaches, become a privileged witness to KwaZulu-Natal's well-preserved flora, fauna, and wildlife, possibly “The Big Five?”

programme.title: From Ithaca to the Amazon
programme.desc: Our natural environments are intrinsically more valuable than any grand visions of wealth created using methods detrimental to the Earth. Meet people in New York, India, Russia, Peru, Sumatra, and South Africa who favor health over profit.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: France's Burgundy and Loire Regions
programme.desc: The Burgundy region boasts top French wines, romantic canals, Romanesque churches, and world-renowned French cuisine. We base in the small town of Beaune and learn about its history of exceptional winemaking. Add a wondrous hot-air balloon ride over the verdant Loire Valley to the itinerary.

programme.title: Berlin
programme.desc: With world-class cultural sites, dynamic new architecture and unstoppable energy, Berlin is a city on the move. We visit the museums - the ancient treasures of the Pergamon and the Egyptian museum, German Expressionism at the Neue Nationalgalerie and the newly designed Jewish Museum.

programme.title: Catalina Island
programme.desc: Catalina Island, California is a unique island off the coast of California, and Donna will take you on a journey there to revel in the island’s history, art, cuisine, and have some fun horseback riding.

programme.title: S8E11 - Prague
programme.desc: We'll visit beautifully preserved Prague to experience its massive castle, evocative Jewish Quarter, thrilling history, infectious music...and perhaps the best beer in Europe.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: S7E2 - Rome: Baroque Brilliance
programme.desc: As we ramble through the heart of Rome, we’ll admire breathtaking Bernini statues and ponder sunbeams inside St. Peter’s Basilica. After dinner, we’ll take a nighttime stroll, lacing together the city’s piazzas and fountains.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: Aarhus
programme.desc: Welcome to Aarhus, Denmark, a city that illuminates the essential societal values Dans hold dear, values that include trust and honesty, health and happiness, and a strong belief in your fellow people. Alexandra comes to find out that collaboration can lead to prosperity.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Eating on the Mekong
programme.desc: Mekong River, Vietnam: On the river, Tony drinks a lot of Mekong moonshine with the welcoming owners of a duck farm. Although seduced by his Vietnam experience, Tony is not sure the royal dish Birds Nest Soup is all its cracked up to be.

programme.title: Lanzhou, On the Yellow River
programme.desc: Travel to Liqian, located at the narrowest point of the Hexi Corridor. Legend states that Liqian is where descendants of Crassus' lost legions ended up. Next, visit the sprawling industrial metropolis of Lanzhou on the Yellow River, and sample an essential ingredient of Chinese culture - noodles.

programme.title: Xi'an, The Capital of the Sons of Heaven
programme.desc: After arriving in Xi’an, you find yourself in the very spot where the caravans of the ancient Silk Road ended their arduous journey. Visit the tomb of Qin Shi Huangdi, the first emperor to rule over a unified China, and discover his terracotta army as it stands guard over him for all eternity.

programme.title: Anatolia, the Caravans of Asia Minor
programme.desc: At the heart of the Anatolian plateau, visit the first of the Caravanserai that once dotted trading stations long the ancient Silk Road. The Caravanserai at Aksaray is the perfect example of architecture representing the Seljuq dynasty, the first empire in the region beginning in the 10th century.

programme.title: Iran: Assassins, Emperors and Magi
programme.desc: Begin in Iran’s Silk Road office where it is made clear that Iran has a goal of linking all countries along the illustrious road together. Then, high above sea level, explore the ruins of Hassan-i Sabbah fortress, the hideout of a movement known as “Hashshashins,” essentially drug smoking assassins.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Tahiti and Bora Bora
programme.desc: For sheer tropical splendor, the islands of Tahiti and Bora Bora stand alone. Hyper blue lagoons, white-sand beaches, fish of every shape, size, and color, as well as a generous and welcoming people make these islands key destinations for travelers from around the world.

programme.title: Polynesia
programme.desc: Experience Polynesia’s rich sea life, crystal blue waters, and vibrant cultures. Tour the diverse reefs of the coral, sea turtle rehabilitation centers, and the many islands and atolls. Participate in the oyster-cultivation process at the major pearl farm, and tour dramatic Marquesas Islands.

programme.title: Montreal
programme.desc: Two of the most unique cities in the world are just north of New England. Here you will find brie, pate, jewel box-patisseries, and “s’il vous plait” right along with bagels, maple syrup, hockey, delis, and bocce ball. Those who forged Montreal and Quebec City braved much to see them flourish.

programme.title: Nova Scotia & Newfoundland
programme.desc: From the charming fishing towns of Nova Scotia to the vast wilderness of Newfoundland, explore the last great open spaces of Eastern North America. A touch of New England, a dash of Germany, here a British fort, there an Irish brogue, the area was peopled by the descendants of hardy colonists.

programme.title: Food, Drink, & Culture
programme.desc: In Istanbul’s Spice Market, brown-gold paprika is carefully molded into pyramids. Cinnamon, cumin, ginger, and cardamom infuse the air. From haggis in Scotland to soba and tea in Japan, from asada in Argentina to bibimbap in Korea, food and drink help illustrate the culture and people of a location.

programme.title: Asian Cities
programme.desc: From the world’s largest city, Tokyo, to the colorful chaos of Delhi, and from the modern miracle of Seoul to the teeming streets of Bangkok, this is your passport to the high-tech marvels and back-street secrets of four of the world’s most amazing cities Asian Cities.

programme.title: Travel Thru History
programme.desc: In this episode we visit the Kennedy Space Center located on Florida's famous Space Coast. We will speak to NASA engineers about the past, present and future of American space travel, as well as take a look at the attractions K.S.C. has to offer.

programme.title: Yellowstone: America's First National Park
programme.desc: Vast, beautiful, and untamed, Yellowstone's wilderness ignites the imagination like no other national park. Get a ringside seat for the geothermal wonders, geyser gazing, and diversity of wildlife that gave Yellowstone the nickname, "America's Serengeti."

programme.title: Italy's Via Cassia
programme.desc: Italy’s Via Cassia once led north from Rome to Florence, finally joining the Via Aurelia at Luna (now Luni). As you meander northward along the ancient route, each unique location you visit, and the interesting people you meet there, speak vividly to the region’s steeped history and culture.

programme.title: Cuba
programme.desc: Cuba is a Caribbean Hotspot. The island is a combination of gorgeous landscapes and a unique way of life. Travel from the Guanahacabibes Peninsula to Guantanamo. In Havana, meet students that wonder about their future prospects: exile or revolution?

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: A Mystical World
programme.desc: Known as Brazil's capital of happiness, Salvador da Bahia offers fruitful local markets, and rich Bahian cuisine. Here, Tony takes part in a traditional local ceremony, and experiences the culinary talents of the famous Bahian artist of the kitchen - Chef Dada.

programme.title: The Struggle for the Soul of America
programme.desc: Tony travels to the grain-belt capital of Minneapolis, Minnesota to experience firsthand the conflict between creative independent operators and generic franchises.

programme.title: Louisville
programme.desc: And we are off! We learn the history of the world famous Kentucky Derby, and call our shot, at one of America's most famous brands, Louisville Slugger. Also, we zip line in the world's only underground zip line attraction, and learn about Muhammad Ali's legacy at the Ali Center.

programme.title: Oslo
programme.desc: Set sail to Oslo, Norway. Climb the fort walls at Akershus Fortress and discover the North and South Poles at the Fram Museum. Then, unearth ancient Viking ship treasures at the Viking Ship Museum, and we will brave the open waters of the Pacific with Thor Heyerdahl at the Kon-tiki museum.

programme.title: Chile - Desert Voices
programme.desc: Known as the driest desert on Earth, the Atacama stretches 1,500 miles along the Andes Cordillera and attracts visitors from all over the world. The intense drought this region experiences helps preserve archaeological sites and geologic features dating back to the origins of the Likan Antai people.

programme.title: Sri Lanka - The Emerald Isle
programme.desc: Sri Lanka is principally known for its heavenly beaches, bold-green mountains and forests, its glorious waterfalls, and renowned tea plantations. It has begun to preserve its ecological resources, and respect the environment more and more, so that everyone may enjoy the land's bounty over time.

programme.title: From Myanmar to Scotland
programme.desc: Biodiversity is a central component to the successful operation of Earth’s natural systems. Meet people from Haiti, Myanmar, Honduras, Kenya, Canada, and Scotland who spend time and energy securing healthy local environmental regulations.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Naples and the Amalfi Coast
programme.desc: Deep in the heart of Naples, Italy is the ideal launching point for exploring Italy's great historic treasures. Marvel at the ancient city of Pompeii, and the eerily captured devastation of Mount Vesuvius. Hop a ferry to the isle of Capri and drive the spectacular Amalfi Coast.

programme.title: Rome
programme.desc: Rudy is in the city where all roads lead - Roma. We begin in ancient Rome - the Forum, Palatine Hill, Colosseum, and the Baths of Caracalla. Then, we explore the modern city of Rome with its ambient life in the streets, cafes, pizzerias and gelaterias.

programme.title: Alberta, Canada
programme.desc: In Alberta, Canada, Donna’s first impression is- snow. And she enjoys it to the fullest. Donna finds myriad ways of taking advantage of a snowy environment, including snow-biking, ice walking, and staying at a world-renowned resort.

programme.title: S8E10 - The Netherlands: Beyond Amsterdam
programme.desc: Zipping from Haarlem to Rotterdam, and from Delft to the former Zuiderzee, we'll enjoy fragrant cheese markets, soggy polderland, charming towns, and windmills both new and old.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: A Desert Feast
programme.desc: Morocco (Sahara): Tony traverses the Moroccan desert with one goal in mind, to eat a mud-oven-roasted sheep.

programme.title: Key West
programme.desc: We are on island time for this episode. Learn about the Key's treasure hunting history at the Mel Fisher Museum. Explore Fort Jefferson, an isolated fort in the Gulf of Mexico that defended the islands. American literature enthusiasts will enjoy a look at Ernest Hemingway's Key West home.

programme.title: S7E3 - Rome: Back-Street Riches
programme.desc: We explore Rome on a more intimate scale — dodging Vespas in Trastevere, roaming through the historic Jewish Ghetto, and enjoying art treasures in a string of rarely visited churches to uncover the charms of hidden Rome.

programme.title: Childhood Flavors
programme.desc: Arcachon, France: Here, Bourdain first learned to love food as a child. Returning for a trip down memory lane, Tony enjoys childhood staples, including steak frites, gaufres (waffles), soupe de pecheur (fisherman's soup) and fresh oysters.

programme.title: Stuffed like a Pig
programme.desc: Portugal & Southwest France: Visiting his boss's family farm, Tony helps slaughter and feast on a pig the family has been fattening all year. Then, Tony heads to France to experience the rich delights of a foie gras farm.

programme.title: Chinguetti
programme.desc: Once at a crossroads of ancient trade routes, the ksar of Chinguetti, Mauritania exists like a pearl in the desert on the western edge of the Sahara Desert, a force of nature whose sand reaches every crook and crevice of life in this land.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Hobart Tasmaina
programme.desc: In Tasmania, Jason immerses himself into the natural world by visiting Cradle Mountain and Weindorfer’s Forest Walk. He also experiences Hobart's cafe culture, and goes on the hunt for fresh seafood.

programme.title: Wild Delicacies
programme.desc: Cambodia: With a friend along for the ride, Tony travels to Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where he explores a food culture that is both pleasing to the palette and slightly frightening.

programme.title: Tabriz, Capital of Merchants
programme.desc: Enter the city that once was the core of the entire Silk Road in Persia: Tabriz, Iran. Find your way into the city’s bazaar, the finest in the country, and wander through its 22-mile labyrinth. Also, meet Dr. Faribouz Esmaeli, the heart of this architectural gem, who oversaw its restoration.

programme.title: Venice, Gateway to the Orient
programme.desc: Just like Marco Polo ages ago, we begin in Venice, Italy. On our journey, we will witness mosaics of St. Mark’s Basilica that reveal links connecting Venice with distant lands in Asia. We will taste Venetian cuisine, and visit an Armenian monastery packed with manuscripts written in all languages.

programme.title: Bosphorus, Astride Two Worlds
programme.desc: At the edge of the European continent, Alfred de Montesquiou enters Turkish territory through the city of Edirne to discover Ottoman architectural wonders and the traditional local sport of oil-wrestling in which men are doused in olive oil before each bout.

programme.title: Of Kings and Gods: The Skyros Horse
programme.desc: This is the story of a mighty horse of legend. The Skyros Horses of Greece are found not only in its hills and plains, but also in its famous monuments such as the Parthenon. For thousands of years the Skyros horse has stood alongside heroes in battle and survives to this day as a Greek treasure.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Down Under: The Wild West of Cooking
programme.desc: Melbourne, Australia boasts hard-living, good-natured, and eccentric lovers of food - Tony's kind of people. In search of the outlaws of food, Tony explores a pasteurization-free cheese factory, and an old-world cured jamon workshop.

programme.title: Thailand, The Andaman Islands
programme.desc: Andaman Coast towns such as Phuket are well known to backpackers and sun seekers. Join Rudy as he paddles through hidden entrances of small islands to find mangroves few people ever see. Also, visit the dramatic limestone cliffs and rock formations jutting out from translucent waters of Phang-nga Bay.

programme.title: Estonia
programme.desc: Venture to Estonia and the islands of Saaremaa and Muhu where you will find windmills, thatch-roofed farmhouses, and quiet waters. Rudy interviews Mart Laar who took over Estonia under tough conditions following the withdrawal of Soviet troops and turned it into a dynamic country.

programme.title: St. Petersburg, Russia
programme.desc: From the splendors of Peterhof to the quiet grace of the city's canals, this former capital built by a czar has reclaimed its position as one of the world's great destinations. St. Petersburg--enjoying a renaissance since its favorite son, Vladimir Putin, ascended to office—has lifted its gloom.

programme.title: Buenos Aires, Argentina
programme.desc: The style and verve of one of South America's most beautiful capitals is highlighted with Argentina's national dance, the tango, as well as the energy that its diverse population brings to the urban landscape. Discover a very special place in Buenos Aires.

programme.title: Mendoza, Argentina
programme.desc: As Rudy ascends into the thin air of the Andes, he stops to visit the graveyard of those who died climbing Aconcagua. Rudy’s next choice for high-altitude adventure? Getting soaked whitewater rafting. Back at sea level he meets winemakers whose elegant Malbecs are shaking up the world's wine market.

programme.title: India: From Girl to Woman
programme.desc: “First marriage and then love.” This Indian proverb describes Indian society quite accurately in terms of how the tradition of marriage is perceived and experienced in the country. In India, people do not just marry whoever they wish. It is the family that decides in an arrangement called Shaadi.

programme.title: Kyoto, Japan
programme.desc: The spiritual heart of Japan, Kyoto offers a glimpse of Japanese life as it used to be, primarily because it was spared during World War II. Comfortable streets with wooden homes, impressive temples, and a dedication to ancient Japanese traditions make Kyoto one of Japan's most visited cities.

programme.title: Yosemite America's Treasure
programme.desc: Experience Yosemite's breathtaking icons like the granite monoliths El Capitan and Half Dome and behold the splendor of Bridal Veil and Yosemite Falls. Explore Yosemite's deep history as the first land set aside for preservation, and a land that inspired John Muir and photographer Ansel Adams.

programme.title: Portugal's Via Publicae
programme.desc: Open your ears to those who call this land home, and who will unveil its unique characteristics to you. Via Publicae was once an ancient Roman road and trade route that stretched from Braga in the north to Lisbon in the south of Portugal. Roman influence was once very strong in this region.

programme.title: The Route of the Two Oceans
programme.desc: The thin ridge that links the two Americas is a miniature world unto itself and concentrates a vast amount of diversity into a small area of land. Follow the Inter-American Highway from Panama City to the Isthmus of Rivas in Nicaragua, the narrowest ridge of Central America.

programme.title: S8E8 - Italy's Verona, Padova, and Ravenna
programme.desc: We'll visit three great cities in the shadow of Venice: Padova (Padua), with its university life and famed basilica; Verona and its Roman ruins; and Ravenna, for its shimmering mosaics.

programme.title: The BBQ Triangle
programme.desc: Which style of BBQ reigns supreme - Kansas City, Houston, or North Carolina? Tony journeys to all three cities to taste for himself the secrets behind sauces, wood pits, and slow smokers.

programme.title: New Orleans
programme.desc: The saints come marching in as we tour the New Orlean's iconic St. Louis Cathedral and the mysterious Ursuline Convent. We see how floats are made and delve into Mardi Gras history at Mardi Gras World. Finally, we visit the National World War II Museum's world-class collection of memorabilia.

programme.title: Flagstaff
programme.desc: Get your kicks on Route 66 in Flagstaff, AZ. Discover the enormous Barringer Meteor Crater. Scan the stars for Planet X at Lowell Observatory, and learn the history of the region at the Northern Arizona History Museum. Finally, swing from ponderosa pines at the Flagstaff Extreme Adventure Park.

programme.title: Madagascar - A Multifaceted Land
programme.desc: Madagascar split off from Africa some 150 million years ago. The isolation of being separated from the mainland caused the island's wildlife to develop distinct and unique features. Once a pirate stronghold, today Madagascar has opened itself up to the world, and is revealing its secrets.

programme.title: Laos - Along The Mekong
programme.desc: Isolated from geopolitics for the past 30 years, Laos is now slowly opening to tourism. Its cultures and environment are fragile, and a responsible form of tourism could preserve its past and character. From fishing villages to the forests of northern Laos, meet the people that protect their land.

programme.title: From Peru to Tanzania
programme.desc: There are places on Earth worthy of absolute preservation and protection for all future generations. Meet people from Puerto Rico, Maryland, Peru, Tanzania, Slovakia, and Cambodia who all share an abiding belief in a sacred, healthy Earth.

programme.title: New Releases
programme.desc: Check out some of our new content!

programme.title: Edinburgh and Scotland
programme.desc: Friendly and feisty, Scotland makes us feel right at home. In Edinburgh, we climb the ramparts of this city's famous castle, shop for kilts, visit mysterious Rosslyn Chapel and gasp on a ghost tour. Then we head to historic St. Andrew's to practice our swing on the world's most famous golf course.

programme.title: Barcelona and Costa Brava
programme.desc: A Mediterranean marvel, Barcelona simmers with beautiful beaches, medieval mazes, eye popping art and hypnotic architecture. From tapas bars, to surrealist art, to Modernist structures, we will feast on Barcelona's delights.

programme.title: Edmonton, Canada
programme.desc: In the second part of her tour of Alberta, Canada, you and Donna will discover fresh cuisine at the local farmer's market and explore some of the region’s crafts. You will also go snowshoeing and learn how to ski.

programme.title: S8E9 - Amsterdam
programme.desc: Uniquely entertaining Amsterdam shows off its Rembrandts and Van Goghs, rivers of bikes, and pot-filled coffeeshops — all under gabled facades leaning out over placid canals.

programme.title: Perth Western Australia
programme.desc: In Western Australia, Jason visits vineyards, goes on a food adventure for crayfishes, truffles, and finger limes, and visits a Brazilian food in Perth city.

programme.title: Traditional Tastes
programme.desc: Morocco (Cities): Tony is invited to experience the culinary heart and distinct walled medinas (districts) of the Moroccan city Fes.

programme.title: Savannah
programme.desc: We visit the old South and enjoy some sweet tea in Savannah. On this episode, we will stroll the city’s beautiful squares, as well as visit its civil war past at Old Fort Jackson. Then, we head up the stairs of the famous Tybee Island lighthouse and visit the Savannah Railroad museum.

programme.title: S7E4 - Florence: Heart of the Renaissance
programme.desc: In Florence, we'll revel in the genius of Michelangelo and Botticelli, climb the dome that kicked off the Renaissance, and cross the Arno to take in modern-day artisan life.

programme.title: The Cook Who Came in From the Cold
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony plays spy in Russia and sets off to locate the best blinis and borscht St. Petersburg has to offer.

programme.title: So Much Vodka, So Little Time
programme.desc: St. Petersburg, Russia: Tony continues his mission with a tour of local working-class specialties. He tries his hand at ice-fishing, drinks a lot of vodka, feasts on Russian foods, eats smoked fish and ends the outing with a dip in the outdoor cold pool.

programme.title: Longyearbyen
programme.desc: Only 650 miles from the North Pole, there are three seasons in Longyearbyen: Polar summer, Northern Lights winter, and Sunny winter, and the elemental side of nature is a common factor in all decisions. The crystalline, light-lit hues of the land can remind one that true spirit shines from within.

programme.title: Curbside Eats
programme.desc: Join hosts Maya Norman and Katrina Kozar as they travel in an R.V. for good food, good drink, and great conversation on Curbside Eats.

programme.title: Melbourne Victoria
programme.desc: Jason catches his own lunch at Buxton trout farm, visits a stone fruit orchard, learns how to make sausages at The Green Olive, and learns secrets of cooking from top Australian chef, Guy Grossi.

programme.title: Eating on the Edge of Nowhere
programme.desc: Cambodia and Japan: Taking his obsession with the film Apocalypse Now a little too seriously, Tony sets out for Pailin, reputed to be one of the most dangerous towns on earth. After his journey, Tony returns to Japan.

programme.title: The New China
programme.desc: China is a young, vibrant culture that is making things happen in the world that will affect everyone. This "inside look" at China by Geographic Travel filmmaker Dale Johnson explores China's explosive double-digit growth that has made it among the world's leading economies, with extra potential.

programme.title: Tarpan: Repainting an Ancient Picture
programme.desc: The Tarpan roamed in wild herds across Europe for millennia, yet the breed became extinct in the 19th century. Today, international teams have introduced a herd of genetically bred, modern Tarpan to remote mountains of Eastern Europe where they hope the horses can find their wild spirits again.

programme.title: Mad Tony: The Food Warrior
programme.desc: Tony embarks on a pilgrimage to Sydney, Australia so he may indulge in a meal made by one of the world's best chefs - Tetsuya Wakuda.

programme.title: Down Under: The Wild West of Cooking
programme.desc: Melbourne, Australia boasts hard-living, good-natured, and eccentric lovers of food - Tony's kind of people. In search of the outlaws of food, Tony explores a pasteurization-free cheese factory, and an old-world cured jamon workshop.

programme.title: Singapore: New York in Twenty Years
programme.desc: Tony sets out to find the real Singapore, with its multicultural restaurants and food markets. He samples prescription food dishes, explores the Geyland Serai Market, and rides the clean and efficient local subway.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Kyushu
programme.desc: Explore the island of Kyushu with it's dramatic landscape and hot sands, and discover the essence of Japanese cuisine with Daisuke Utagawa and Rudy Maxa.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Tokyo
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take us to the heart of Japan in Tokyo where culinary geniuses strive for perfection as they prepare everything from sushi to the wasabi.

programme.title: Taste of Japan: Hokkaido
programme.desc: Rudy Maxa and Daisuke Utagawa take you to Japan's northern frontier Hokkaido. The hot spring capital of Japan with its many volcanoes, Hokkaido also boosts some of the world greatest ramen, ramen noodles, and legendary whiskey.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 1
programme.desc: Host Rudy Maxa and Washington, D.C. restaurateur and chef Daisuke Utagawa enthusiastically eat their way through Hong Kong, from cheap but authentic, hole-in-the-wall Chinese restaurants to Michelin-starred palaces. Along the way they illustrate the excitement and energy that defines Hong Kong.

programme.title: Hong Kong, Part 2
programme.desc: Dramatic photography by renowned shooters Karel Bauer and Joe Pontecorvo bring Hong Kong into viewers' homes as never before. Stray from the iconic photo of Hong Kong as a wall of skyscrapers against Victoria Peak with the city's harbor in a foreground and visits the other side of the island.

programme.title: Bangkok
programme.desc: Washington, DC, restaurateur Daisuke Utagawa and travel journalist Rudy Max deliver viewers directly to Bangkok’s sprawling city temples, its huge flower market, its vibrant klongs (canals), and to its most interesting cuisine, all of which made Bangkok the world’s most-visited city by travelers.

programme.title: Las Vegas
programme.desc: Explore Las Vegas’ lesser known past. We visit the National Atomic Testing museum to learn about how the desert outside of Vegas was used for testing America’s secret nuclear weapons. We also visit the Mormon Fort, the first permanent non-native settlement in the area, as well as the Neon Museum.

programme.title: Wild National Parks
programme.desc: From grizzly bears of Katmai National Park in Alaska to rattlesnakes of Montezuma's Castle in Arizona, answer the call of America's wildest national parks. By land, sea, and sky, get up close to creatures of all shapes and sizes. Dedicated park workers reveal what it takes to nurture nature.

programme.title: The Mohawk Trail Across New England
programme.desc: The Mohawk Trail is deeply embedded in the history of America. For many years it served as a main trade route for indigenous tribes. As European settlement expanded, the Mohawk Trail began to change as the country itself changed. Tap into one of America’s richest springs of historical significance.

programme.title: Sri Lanka: Monsoon Island

programme.title: The Hebrides: Land of Legends
programme.desc: The Hebrides archipelago is made up of more than 500 islands and islets, lying just off the coast of west Scotland. Isolation has made it the perfect breeding ground for millions of creatures.

programme.title: Japan: Islands of Extremes
programme.desc: Japan’s 7,000 islands stretch for over 2,400km, and cover an incredible range of climates. Winter in the northern islands can be savage, but summer in the southern islands couldn’t be more different.

programme.title: Surviving in the Lagoon

programme.title: Water Works

programme.title: Shanghai Super Tower

programme.title: Stoked on Fishing - An Unforgettable Trip, South Lake, Part Two
programme.desc: This show was filmed in late October of 2019. Four months prior, in June of 2019, Tim Carnahan was diagnosed with Glioblastoma, Brain Cancer. According to Tim's medical team, his life expectancy could be between three months and 18 months. Fast forward to now, 2020; today's update is one we hoped would never come. With a heavy heart and tear-filled eyes, we share with you that Tim Carnahan has passed away after battling for close to 12 months. It only fits that the last words to pass his lips were I love you, Lory, and keep fishing. While his time on earth was cut short, the amount of joy he experienced and shared with others was genuinely tremendous and will never be forgotten. If you would like to help out in any way, lory and friends have put together a Go Fund Me page to ease the financial burden of medical bills and afford lory some time to greave and transition into life without Tim. We love you, Tim. Rest in peace, buddy.

programme.title: VW Golf

He truly is an icon of German and international motorsports when it comes to car racing.

programme.title: Tour Car Price Argentina

Underbody and axles are also optimized once more. The service car is ready to roll and the hardware of the German team is shipped to Buenos Aires. The team members draw up their summary so far.

programme.title: Audi Quattro
programme.desc: The Audi quattro changed the car world forever. For the first time, a four-wheel-drive is not only deployed in a production car, but also in a rally car. Car History shows the evolution of the Audi quattro from its beginnings as a sports coupe to the S1 and S2, the most spectacular rally cars ever built. Rally world champion Walter Rohrl also shares his experiences with the quattro.

programme.title: Alfa Romeo - The quest for the original Giulietta
programme.desc: Nowadays, the mother of all Alfa Romeo Giuliettas is a sought-after but very rare specimen among collectors. We accompany the Alfa expert and collector Hartmut Stoppel with his new Giulietta in search of the original oldtimer in the Italian region of Piedmont.

programme.title: Fascination Nurburgring
programme.desc: The Historic Trophy at the Nurburgring race track featured classic cars from past eras of motorsports. Also: with the M3, BMW brought race car technology to the streets. It was a versatile car, suitable for the city, the country and the highway. And it left an impressive mark at the DTM as well. And: in 1987, the Ford Sierra RS Cosworth taught its racing competition the meaning of fear.

programme.title: Land Rover
programme.desc: The Land Rover is the bedrock of all terrain vehicles. Built in 1948 as a simple car for British farmers, the Land Rover soon became an export hit. Two years later the all-rounder was sold in over 70 countries. Today the Landy is at home all over the world. Car History highlights the story of Land Rover, which evolved into a luxury manufacturer with the introduction of the Range Rover.

programme.title: Audi Quattro - The Rally Classic

And: Mercedes-Benz' Unimog concept car.

programme.title: Ken Block in the Rally Cross World Cup

In this episode, the Subaru XV shows its offroad skills, and the Nissan Juke is taken to the race track in Dubai. And: the crown princes of compact SUVs, the Mercedes-AMG and the Audi RS Q3 GLA face each other in the mountains.

US-Americans don't want to miss out on space, comfort and loading capacity. Their motto is: the bigger, the better. Chevrolet Suburban, Jeep Cherokee, GMC Yukon, we show you the world of US offroaders.

programme.title: Mercedes Motorsport - Rally
programme.desc: Wether it is the Rallye Monte Carlo, the European Rallye Championship or the Street Grand Prix of Argentina, there was a time when Mercedes did dominate the international rallye scene with cars like the sluggish 180D or the heavy touring saloons 220 or 300SE. Hardly anybody knows that, after retirering from Formula 1 and Le Mans, starting at the end of the fifties Mercedes is using the Rallyesport for a long time as a testing ground since the use of production-close cars is mandatory then.

programme.title: Mercedes 280 SE meets America - Florida

Even though the brand disappeared, the legend lives on amongst car enthusiasts. Tillmann Miritz finds old Rivoltas with Corvette V8 engines on his road trip to the Sarasota Classic Car Museum in Florida. There Renzo Rivolta’s nephews build new cars, too, but this time for water.

programme.title: Kymco People GT 300i - Review & Test Drive
programme.desc: 10 or 16 inch wheels - is this really just a question of taste? MOTORVISION TV reveals the advantages and disadvantages of the big wheel motorcycle People GT 300i, made by Kymco.

During his search for these American dream cars of the 60s Tillmann Miritz makes a surprise discovery in Florida. Revology Cars are upgrading original 1964 Ford Mustang chassis with modern technology and engines.

He successfully took part in several international races like the 24 Hours of Le Mans or the James Hardy 1000 for the Porsche and BMW brands, and he still remains involved with the BMW racing team as an adviser after ending his career in 1998.

programme.title: Chris Pfeiffer reviews the BMW F 800 R

Adrenaline-pumped stunts with lots of crashes are guaranteed!

And: after World War II, Mercedes-Benz returned to the luxury class with its 170 S cabriolet.

programme.title: Arabella Classics
programme.desc: Rare Automobiles and stunning views! The Arabella Classics, one of the most exclusive Classic Car Rallies in Europe.

Rally world champion Walter Rohrl also shares his experiences with the quattro.

With more than 600 hp these luxurious power packs make for an almost transcendental driving experience and deliver the perfect combination of elegance and performance, for those who can afford such extravagant luxury.

programme.title: Lifestyle SUVs
programme.desc: The desert, an endless horizon, green highlands and rugged hills. In Morocco, you can find the dream landscapes from 1001 nights. We took the Porsche Macan Turbo on a trip through the fascinating city of Marrakesh and the beautiful countryside. In addition: the BMW X 6M, one of the pioneers in the very trendy SUV coupe segment.

programme.title: Cops in the Fast Lane
programme.desc: In a city that loves to show off wealth and luxury, the Dubai police are eager to represent this image via its fleet of patrol cars that includes a Chevrolet Camaro, a Lamborghini Aventador, a Bentley GT, a Ferrari FF, an Aston Martin and a Mercedes SLS. For the first time ever, the Dubai Police Special Cars Unit allowed a television crew to accompany them on their service missions.

programme.title: V8 Open
programme.desc: What better way is there to celebrate a stylish and powerful car and a sunny summer day than going for a cruise over the Alps to Italy in a Maserati GranCabrio MC? In addition: a Brit with a fiery temperament, the Jaguar XK-RS convertible with 550 hp. And: Mercedes AMG's SL models, uncompromising performance.

programme.title: Car Tales from High Desert in California
programme.desc: On his journey to Las Vegas Marco drops by Big Mike in the Apple Valley, a remote area in the High Desert of California. Together they meet Big Mike’s bizarre friends from the Lowdown Kustos family, which once have been trendsetters of the Californian car customizing scene. Afterwards he gets involved with Big Mike’s scary Bike Buddies, when they ride through the dessert spreading fear and panic.

programme.title: Plenty of Luxury in the Cadillac CT6
programme.desc: Cadillac wants to occupy a permanent place in the segment of the upper-class sedans, which is dominated by German manufacturers. The CT6 can stand out from the other models especially with its design.

programme.title: SEMA, Las Vegas - Part 1
